channel.title: Java problem
channel.description:
I was having trouble before with my java..then i fixed it and fixed my jdk for the compiling but then this came up. And i don't know what it means. I thought it was just a source problem but yeah...Would anyone be kind enough to point me in the right direction?
[IMG]http://i56.tinypic.com/2v2fq4k.png[/img]

item.title: Java problem
item.dc:creator: @zyle1992 Zymus
item.description:
@zyle1992 wrote:

[quote=“vs banshee, post:5, topic:417843”][quote author=zyle1992 link=topic=520392.msg3779282#msg3779282 date=1318322299]

#facepalm…the what? Im still in the process of learning. So i don’t know much sorry :l

The code of the file you’re running (the .bat file) compile.bat or something similar.
[/quote]

It was my compiler.

" @echo off
“C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_27\bin\javac.exe” -d bin -cp clientlibs.jar -sourcepath . *.java
pause "

it happen’s with every source i try to use.[/quote]

  1. Remove all traces of Java (both JRE and JDK)
  2. Install Java 7 (JDK)

It should work after that. It sounds like a bad install. I’m feeling generous tonight, so I might be able to help via Teamviewer.
